    "height": "auto"
  })), mdx("br", null), mdx("h1", null, "MINI GAMES AND THEIR STORYLINES"), mdx("h2", null, "Life Stories Storyline"), mdx("p", null, "The story of how you become famous with your social app: the goals, obstacles, raised stakes, twists, and gameplay changes"), mdx("p", null, "LS1.0 Meet \u201CThe Word\u201D, learn the game"), mdx("p", null, "LS2.0 Meet The Nose"), mdx("p", null, "LS3.0 Learn island background"), mdx("p", null, "LS4.0 Clues that The Nose works for the Maestro and clues that he is a goodguy"), mdx("p", null, "You become an important person on the island when you introduce your social app called \u201Cthe word\u201D. The app helps you meet people in person (usually the town square) and make friends (in other words, play Life Stories). After you chat with the person (play the game), they are added to your list of friends. The app also counts the number of times you have played with them. You gain influence on the island by collecting numbers of friends and/or strengths of friendships.\nAfter the game, you evaluate your new friend\u2019s personality by going down a list of 4-7 dichotomies and selecting either\u2026\nIdeas person \u2190 \u2192 People person\nValues achievement \u2190 \u2192 Values enjoyment\nIdealist \u2190 \u2192 Realist\nHumorous \u2190 \u2192 Informative\nEt cetera \u2190 \u2192 And so on"), mdx("p", null, "After you rate the other player, you get to see a bar graph of how others rated them. This personality rating is \u201Cthe word\u201D on your new friend. If your opinion of that person changes in subsequent games, you can change your answers.\nThe purpose of this personality rating is to make \u201Cthe word\u201D unique among social apps (thus making it a believable plot point), to make Life Stories more fun, to make our version of the game more original, to make you really get to know other players, to influence how NPCs talk to you, and maybe\u2014in version 3.0\u2014to affect the course of the story line."), mdx("p", null, "In addition to the personality test, you would also evaluate their language level."), mdx("br", null), mdx("h2", null, "Card Game Storyline"), mdx("p", null, "The story of how you become rich: the obstacles, triumphs, raised stakes, twists, and game changes"), mdx("p", null, "We need to think of ways gameplay will change, then base the story on that."), mdx("p", null, "GW1.0 Meet Raj Raja, learn the game:\nHow you will earn Shells\nHow you will gain objects"), mdx("p", null, "GW2.0 Learn Raja\u2019s Backstory"), mdx("p", null, "GW3.0 Get promoted"), mdx("p", null, "GW4.0 Clues that Mr Raja is the Maestro and clues that he is a good guy."), mdx("br", null), mdx("h3", null, "Card Game Mechanics"), mdx("p", null, mdx("strong", {
    parentName: "p"
  }, "Game Flow"), "\nThe game is played with Blue Team versus Red Team. Each team consists of two players. One team may be computer controlled. The objective of the game is to deplete the enemy player\u2019s HP pools to zero. The game begins with the setup phase."), mdx("p", null, mdx("strong", {
    parentName: "p"
  }, "Setup Phase"), "\nThe Game Board is populated. The Game Board looks like this:"), mdx("center", null, "\n  ", mdx("img", {
    parentName: "center",
    "src": "https://i.imgur.com/a/eyBiqI9.png",
    "width": "50%",
    "height": "auto"
  })), mdx("p", null, "Red and Orange are red team, and Blue and Light Blue are blue team.\nThe striped cards are the locations for the player\u2019s Decks.\nThe dotted cards are the player\u2019s selected Identities. This will mirror the chosen card on on the player\u2019s Bench, represented by the thick-lined cards. The card chosen as the Identity will still be displayed on the bench. Players will not be able to see the Identity cards of the opposing team."), mdx("p", null, "The player\u2019s deck consists of 15 - 60 cards.\nTwo thirds of the cards are always Noun cards\nOne third is always Modifier cards"), mdx("p", null, "When the player first learns the game with an NPC during the introduction, they are given the choice of starting with one of three basic, pre-assembled decks (these are temporary options and can be changed later):\nPeople\nFruits\nAnimals"), mdx("p", null, "As the players play the game and earn new cards, they will find cards in a much wider variety of categories, and be able to build their own decks."), mdx("p", null, "Before the game begins, decks are automatically shuffled by the game engine. Each player will be give 5 Noun cards from their deck, determined at random. These cards are placed on the Bench."), mdx("p", null, "Each player will choose one of the cards to be their first Identity."), mdx("p", null, "All players begin with 20 Points in their HP Pool."), mdx("p", null, "The two players on the Red Team and those on the Blue Team have their Diligence statistics added together. The team with the higher combination goes first."), mdx("p", null, "This concludes the Setup Phase."), mdx("br", null), mdx("h3", null, "Team Turn Phase"), mdx("p", null, "The remainder of the game alternates between the two teams. A turn should take 45-60 seconds. If a turn takes longer than the maximum amount of time, the turn is forfeit, and it becomes the other team\u2019s turn."), mdx("p", null, "The following outlines describes the order in which a player\u2019s turn takes place:"), mdx("p", null, mdx("strong", {
    parentName: "p"
  }, "Draw a Card"), " - each of the players on the team draws a card from their own deck or from their partner\u2019s deck. This should be coordinated between the players via voice chat.\nIf no cards remain in the player\u2019s deck, he must draw from his partner\u2019s deck.\nIf neither player on the team has cards remaining in their deck, no cards are drawn.\nIf the card is a Noun card, it will be placed on the bench.\nIf the card is a Noun card but the player has no room on the bench, they may discard the new card, or any card currently on the bench. The player cannot discard their current Identity.\nIf the card is a Modifier card, it may be applied to the current Identity, given to the player\u2019s partner\u2019s Identity, or discarded."), mdx("p", null, mdx("strong", {
    parentName: "p"
